  "original_title": "\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bcd - \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Steps to increase Jaffna-Colombo train services",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena has said that steps will be taken to increase freight train services to Jaffna and Colombo and Fort in the future.",
        "The minister, who is on a two-day official visit to Jaffna, reached Kangesanturai railway station yesterday (21) by 'Jaffna Rani' train.",
        "Speaking to the media, he said that for the first time in history, more services have been started considering the people of Jaffna.",
        "He said that activities like 'Jaffa Rani' train service between Kangesanthurai - Kilinochchi Science City, suspended night mail train service, Uttaradevi and Kadukathi services have been increased. (a)"
      ],
